<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Issuer Cooperation Dashboard — Recupero</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
<style>
  /* Cooperation dashboard — operator-facing overview of every
     issuer's cross-case freeze-letter history. Designed to live in
     the operator's pinned tabs as the strategy reference document. */
  .dash-stat-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    margin: 24px 0 32px;
  }
  .dash-stat {
    background: #fafafa;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold-accent);
    padding: 14px 18px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .dash-stat-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ink-quiet);
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }
  .dash-stat-value {
    display: block;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .instrument-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .instrument-pill.standard   { background: #DCFCE7; color: #14532D; }
  .instrument-pill.le_backed  { background: #DBEAFE; color: #1E3A8A; }
  .instrument-pill.fincen_314b { background: #FEF3C7; color: #5C2D0F; }
  .instrument-pill.mlat       { background: #FED7AA; color: #5C1F09; }
  .instrument-pill.subpoena   { background: #FECACA; color: #7F1D1D; }
  .black-hole-row { background: #fef2f2; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Operator Intelligence</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Internal · Operator Reference</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Cross-case strategy reference</div>
    <h1>Issuer Cooperation<br/>Dashboard</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Aggregated freeze-letter history across every Recupero case
      to date. Each row records the issuer's actual response patterns
      and the recommended legal instrument for the next case naming
      that issuer. Refresh by re-running
      <span class="mono">recupero-ops cooperation-dashboard</span>.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="dash-stat-grid">
  <div class="dash-stat">
    <span class="dash-stat-label">Issuers tracked</span>
    <span class="dash-stat-value">{{ stats.n_issuers }}</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dash-stat">
    <span class="dash-stat-label">Letters on file</span>
    <span class="dash-stat-value">{{ stats.n_letters_total }}</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dash-stat">
    <span class="dash-stat-label">Total frozen (USD)</span>
    <span class="dash-stat-value">{{ stats.total_frozen_usd_human }}</span>
  </div>
  <div class="dash-stat">
    <span class="dash-stat-label">Black-hole issuers</span>
    <span class="dash-stat-value">{{ stats.n_black_holes }}</span>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Per-issuer cooperation profile</h2>
<p class="small">
  Sorted by letter volume DESC. Issuers below the confidence threshold
  (&lt;3 letters) appear at the bottom with their numbers suppressed.
  The "Recommended instrument" column is the suggested legal channel
  for the next freeze request to that issuer, derived from cooperation
  history + jurisdiction + sanctions exposure (the recommender does
  NOT know whether the next case is OFAC-exposed — that signal layers
  on at the per-case LE handoff Section 5.7 level).
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Issuer</th>
      <th>Letters</th>
      <th>Response rate</th>
      <th>Median response</th>
      <th>Full freeze rate</th>
      <th>Total frozen</th>
      <th>Recommended instrument</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for prof in profiles %}
    <tr{% if prof.is_black_hole %} class="black-hole-row"{% endif %}>
      <td><strong>{{ prof.issuer }}</strong>
        {% if prof.is_black_hole %}
        <br/><span class="small" style="color:#991b1b;font-weight:600">⚠ BLACK HOLE</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
      <td>{{ prof.n_letters_sent }}</td>
      <td>
        {% if prof.has_confident_profile %}
        {{ "%.0f%%"|format(prof.response_rate * 100) }}
        {% else %}<span class="small secondary">n/a</span>{% endif %}
      </td>
      <td>
        {% if prof.median_response_hours is not none %}
        {{ "%.0f"|format(prof.median_response_hours) }}h
        {% else %}—{% endif %}
      </td>
      <td>
        {% if prof.has_confident_profile %}
        {{ "%.0f%%"|format(prof.full_freeze_rate * 100) }}
        {% else %}—{% endif %}
      </td>
      <td class="amount">{{ prof.total_frozen_usd_human }}</td>
      <td>
        <span class="instrument-pill {{ prof.recommended_instrument }}">
          {{ prof.recommended_instrument }}
        </span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

{% if stats.n_black_holes > 0 %}
<h2>Black-hole issuers</h2>
<p>
  These issuers have received three or more informal freeze requests
  across prior cases with zero responses of any kind. For future
  cases naming these issuers, the recommendation is to skip the
  informal channel entirely and proceed directly to a grand jury
  subpoena via the cooperating AUSA.
</p>
<ul>
  {% for prof in profiles if prof.is_black_hole %}
  <li>
    <strong>{{ prof.issuer }}</strong> —
    {{ prof.n_letters_sent }} letters, 0 responses
    {% if prof.latest_letter_sent_at %}
    (most recent: {{ prof.latest_letter_sent_at[:10] }})
    {% endif %}
  </li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
{% endif %}

<h2>Methodology notes</h2>
<p class="small">
  <strong>Response rate</strong> is the share of letters that produced
  at least one non-silence outcome (acknowledged / declined /
  partial_freeze / full_freeze / etc.) — it measures whether the
  issuer engages at all, not whether the engagement was favorable.
  <strong>Full freeze rate</strong> is the share of letters that
  produced a <code>full_freeze</code> or <code>returned_to_victim</code>
  outcome. <strong>Median response</strong> is the time-to-first-
  response across letters that received a response (silent letters
  excluded from the timing aggregate).
</p>
<p class="small">
  The <strong>confidence threshold</strong> for surfacing per-issuer
  percentages is three letters. Below that, the response_rate /
  full_freeze_rate columns show "n/a" rather than a misleadingly
  precise figure derived from a sample of one or two.
</p>
<p class="small">
  This dashboard is generated from
  <code>public.freeze_letters_sent</code> joined to
  <code>public.freeze_outcomes</code> — the same data substrate that
  feeds Section 5.7 of each per-case LE handoff. Refresh after any
  significant batch of new outcomes lands.
</p>

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Operator Intelligence</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Internal Operator Reference.</span>
    Not for distribution to issuer compliance teams, victims, or
    counterparties. The numbers in this document are derived from
    Recupero's full case history and would compromise the strategic
    advantage that history provides if shared externally.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
